Definition: a primitive root; to spill forth (blood, a libation, liquid metal; or even a solid, i.e. to mound up); also (figuratively) to expend (life, soul, complaint, money, etc.); intensively, to sprawl out; cast (up), gush out, pour (out), shed(-der, out), slip.
from {{h8210}}; an emptying place, e.g. an ash-heap; are poured out.
feminine of a derivative from {{h8210}}; a pipe (for pouring forth, e.g. wine), i.e. the penis; privy member.
a primitive root; to depress or sink (especially figuratively, to humiliate, intransitive or transitive); abase, bring (cast, put) down, debase, humble (self), be (bring, lay, make, put) low(-er).
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h8213}}; abase, humble, put down, subdue.
(Aramaic) from {{h8214}}; low; basest.
from {{h8213}}; an humble rank; low estate (place).
from {{h8213}}; depressed, literally or figuratively; base(-st), humble, low(-er, -ly).
feminine of {{h8216}}; depression; low place.
from {{h8213}}; Lowland, i.e. (with the article) the maritime slope of Palestine; low country, (low) plain, vale(-ley).
probably abridged from {{h3474}}; plain; Sharon, the name of a place in Palestine; Lasharon, Sharon.
from {{h8308}}; a thong (as laced or tied); (shoe-)latchet.
probably from {{h8281}} (in the sense of dwelling (compare {{h8271}}) and {{h2580}}; abode of pleasure; Sharuchen, a place in Palestine; Sharuhen.
from {{h8276}}; tendril; Serug, a postdiluvian patriarch; Serug.
from {{h8324}} in its original sense of pressing; a wrist-band (as compact or clasping); bracelet.
probably feminine of {{h7791}}; a fortification (literally or figuratively); sing (by mistake for {{h7891}}), wall.
the same as {{h8282}}; Sarah, Abraham's wife; Sarah.
feminine of {{h8269}}; a mistress, i.e. female noble; lady, princess, queen.
a primitive root; to free; direct.
a primitive root; to prevail; have power (as a prince).
a primitive root; to ogle, i.e. blink coquettishly; wanton.
a primitive root; to course (like a beast of prey); by implication, to seek greedily; have appetite, justle one against another, long, range, run (to and fro).
from {{h8266}}; an untruth; by implication, a sham (often adverbial); without a cause, deceit(-ful), false(-hood, -ly), feignedly, liar,   lie, lying, vain (thing), wrongfully.
a primitive root; to cheat, i.e. be untrue (usually in words); fail, deal falsely, lie.
passive participle of {{h8259}}; (compare {{h8260}}); an embrasure or opening	with bevelled jam; light, window.
from {{h8259}}; a loophole (for looking out), to admit light and air; window.
from {{h8262}}; filth, i.e. (figuratively and specifically) an idolatrous object; abominable(-tion).
a primitive root; to be filthy, i.e. (intensively) to loathe, pollute; abhor, make abominable, have in abomination, detest, × utterly.
from {{h8323}}; a head person (of any rank or class); captain (that had rule), chief (captain), general, governor, keeper, lord,(-task-)master, prince(-ipal), ruler, steward.
from {{h8248}}; a trough (for watering); trough.
probably from {{h8324}}; hostile; Sharay, an Israelite; Sharai.
from {{h8276}}; a tendril (as entwining); branch.
patrial from {{h8289}}; a Sharonite or inhabitant of Sharon; Sharonite.
passive participle from the same as {{h8321}}; a grapevine; principal plant. See {{h8320}}, {{h8321}}.
or (by permutation) שְׁרִיקָה; feminine passive participle of {{h8319}}; a whistling (in scorn); by analogy, a piping; bleating, hissing.
from {{h8281}} abbreviated; freedom; remnant.
by permutation for {{h5629}}; superfluity; Serach, an Israelitess; Sarah, Serah.
a primitive root; to gash; cut in pieces, make [cuttings] pieces.
and שָׂרֶטֶת; from {{h8295}}; an incision; cutting.
from {{h8269}}; dominative; Sarai, the wife of Abraham; Sarai.
a primitive root; to intwine; wrap together, wreath.
a primitive root; (compare {{h8279}}); properly, to puncture, i.e. (figuratively through the idea of slipping out) to escape or survive; remain.
from {{h8273}} and {{h3050}}; Jah has brought heat; Sherebjah, the name of two Israelites; Sherebiah.
for {{h7626}}; a rod of empire; sceptre.
of foreign derivation; Sharetser, the name of an Assyrian and an Israelite; Sharezer.
from an unused root meaning to glare; quivering glow (of the air), especially the mirage; heat, parched ground.
from {{h8324}}; (compare {{h8306}}); a string (as twisted ), i.e. (specifically) the umbilical cord (also figuratively, as the centre of strength); navel.
(Aramaic) a root corresponding to that of {{h8293}}; to free, separate; figuratively, to unravel, commence; by implication (of unloading beasts) to reside; begin, dissolve, dwell, loose.
from {{h8277}}; stitching (as pierced with a needle); service.
from {{h8277}}; a (carpenter's) scribing-awl (for pricking or scratching measurements); line.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h7785}}; the leg; leg.
from {{h8264}}; properly, a mesh (as allowing a liquid to run through), i.e. coarse loose cloth or sacking (used in mourning and for bagging); hence, a bag (for grain, etc.); sack(-cloth, -clothes).
from {{h7857}} (for alliteration with {{h7110}}); an outburst (of anger); little.
from {{h8239}}; a (double) stall (for cattle); also a (two-pronged) hook (for flaying animals on); hook, pot.
from {{h8245}}; the almond (tree or nut; as being the earliest in bloom); almond (tree).
a denominative from {{h8247}}; to be (intensively, make) almond-shaped; make like (unto, after the fashion of) almonds.
a primitive root; to be alert, i.e. sleepless; hence to be on the lookout (whether for good or ill); hasten, remain, wake, watch (for).
a primitive root; to fasten; bind.
from {{h8248}}; (plural collective) a draught; drink.
a primitive root; to quaff, i.e. (causatively) to irrigate or furnish a potion to; cause to (give, give to, let, make to) drink, drown, moisten, water. See {{h7937}}, {{h8354}}.
from {{h8257}}; a depression; hollow strake.
a primitive root; properly, to lean out (of a window), i.e. (by implication) peep or gaze (passively, be a spectacle); appear, look (down, forth, out).
a primitive root; to suspend or poise (especially in trade); pay, receive(-r), spend, × throughly, weigh.
from {{h8254}}; probably a weight; used as a commercial standard; shekel.
or (feminine) שִׁקְמָה; of uncertain derivation; a sycamore (usually the tree); sycamore (fruit, tree).
(abbreviated Amos 8:8); a primitive root; to subside; by implication, to be overflowed, cease; causatively, to abate, subdue; make deep, let down, drown, quench, sink.
from {{h8248}}; a beverage; moisture, i.e. (figuratively) refreshment; drink, marrow.
or שִׁקֻּץ; from {{h8262}}; disgusting, i.e. filthy; especially idolatrous or (concretely) an idol; abominable filth (idol, -ation), detestable (thing).
a primitive root; to repose (usually figurative); appease, idleness, (at, be at, be in, give) quiet(-ness), (be at, be in, give, have, take) rest, settle, be still.
from {{h8252}}; tranquillity; quietness.
from {{h8277}}; a survivor; × alive, left, remain(-ing), remnant, rest.
feminine of {{h8228}}; copiousness; abundance, company, multitude.
from an unused root meaning to abound; resources; abundance.
probably from {{h8192}}; bare spot; Shepham, a place in or near Palestine; Shepham.
from {{h8213}}; remissness; idleness.
formed like {{h8221}}; baldly; Shapham, an Israelite; Shapham.
from {{h8193}}; the beard (as a lip-piece); beard, (upper) lip.
patrial from {{h8221}}; a Shiphmite or inhabitant of Shepham; Shiphmite.
feminine plural of {{h8221}}; Siphmoth, a place in Palestine; Siphmoth.
from {{h8226}}; a species of rock-rabbit (from its hiding), i.e. probably the hyrax; coney.
a primitive root; to conceal (as a valuable); treasure.
(Aramaic) from {{h8231}}; the dawn (as brilliant with aurora); × very early in the morning.
a primitive root; to locate, i.e. (generally) hang on or (figuratively) establish, reduce; bring, ordain, set on.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h8231}}; to be beautiful; be acceptable, please,   think good.
from {{h8231}}; beauty; × goodly.
from {{h8228}}; copious; Shiphi, an Israelite; Shiphi.
a primitive root; to glisten, i.e. (figuratively) be (causatively, make) fair; × goodly.
the same as {{h8235}}; Shiphrah, an Israelitess; Shiphrah.
from {{h8231}}; splendid, i.e. a tapestry or canopy; royal pavilion.
the same as {{h8233}}; Shepher, a place in the Desert; Shapper.
from {{h8231}}; brightness; garnish.
from an unused root meaning the same as {{h7779}}; a kind of serpent (as snapping), probably the cerastes or horned adder; adder.
plural of an unused noun from the same as {{h8207}} and meaning the same; serpents; Shuppim, an Israelite; Shuppim.
from {{h8192}}; bareness; concretely, a bare hill or plain; high place, stick out.
from {{h8199}}; judge-like; Shiphtan, an Israelite; Shiphtan.
or שְׁפַטְיָהוּ; from {{h8199}} and {{h3050}}; Jah has judged; Shephatjah, the name of ten Israelites; Shephatiah.
from {{h8199}}; judge; Shaphat, the name of four Israelites; Shaphat.
from {{h8199}}; a sentence, i.e. infliction; judgment.
(Aramaic) intensive of a form corresponding to {{h8208}}; beautiful; fair.
from {{h8231}}; beautiful; Shaphir, a place in Palestine; Saphir.
